On 2 Nov 2012, at 04:10, Kerry Mockler <kbryna@gmail.com> wrote:

> oh there's a picture book of Mary Anning and her fossils, which I believe
> includes her displaying them herself, and does (I think) have at least one
> page about where they end up - in museums.
> 
> There is also a book (nonfiction) that I loved as a kid about items from
> the smithsonian - it's called Auks, Rocks and the Odd Dodo (pub 1985 -
> maybe out of print now). It's about the Natural History Museum and how its
> exhibits are assembled - behind the scenes kind of stuff.
> 
> This IS a great list to come up with - I hope you'll post the final list!
